    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen I open nvim with \"nvim xxx.lua\", BufRead autocmd can not trigger\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```shell\r\n$ echo \"syntax on | autocmd BufRead * :echomsg 'BufRead'\" > a.vim\r\n$ touch a.lua\r\n$ nvim -u a.vim a.lua # run :mes<CR>, no messages\r\n$ nvim -u a.vim a.vim # run :mes<CR>, have one message\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nwhen I run `nvim -u a.vim a.lua`, can see `BufRead` message in cmdline\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 12.7.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2 3.4.23\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ndowload from release web page",
